# config/user_email_map.txt.example
# SANITIZED TEMPLATE (see config/SITE_OVERRIDE.md).
# Real copy: config/site/user_email_map.txt (gitignored).
# Deployed to: /etc/biome-calc/conf/user_email_map.txt
# ============================================================================
# USER EMAIL OVERRIDE MAP
# ============================================================================
# Format: <username>  <email>   (one per row; separator = spaces/tabs)
# Blank lines and lines starting with '#' are ignored.
#
# DEFAULT BEHAVIOUR (no entry here):
#   resolve_user_email() uses MAIL_DOMAINS_USER (setup_nodes.vars.conf) and
#   notifies every active domain. The relay silently absorbs bounces.
#
# ADD AN OVERRIDE WHEN:
#   - the AD username != the email local-part (service accounts, legacy aliases)
#   - you want to force a SINGLE address
#   - a user asks not to receive copies on multiple domains
#
# EXAMPLES:
#   jdoe                  j.doe@example.org
#   astudent              astudent@students.example.org
#   svc-bot               ops@example.org
# ============================================================================
